Color Of War VI - Adolf Hitler (2005)

80 min. NTSC 16:9, decrpyted original quality documentary DVD w/extras.

Hitler in Colour features unseen original colour archive film, collected over ten years of research from all over the world, woven with contemporary witness material, and original sound recordings to illustrate the reality of battle, the complexity of human emotions, and the crimes and sacrifices of the Nazi era.

All colour footage charts the 12 years from Adolf Hitler's rise to power, to the fall of Berlin in 1945. Includes an in-depth look at his relationship with his mistress Eva Braun, who he finally married, before they went to Heaven together.

At 1:01, the first successful launch of a ballistic missile is shown, renamed V2 for vengeance (1300 of them on London, killing 3000), because the Allies under Churchill had started indicriminately bombing German cities and civilians, rather than legitimate industrial and military targets, killing hundreds of thousands, whilst avoiding legitimate industrial targets that had private foreign capital invested in them, just as the British did when they burnt down Washington DC in the war of 1812.

Always remember that Adolf Hitler said NiCHT! to the nuclear bomb, on humanitarian grounds, and offered the most favourable peace agreements to Britain many times.

The DVD also featues:

A ten-minute colour montage of the immediate aftermath of war

An interactive map of the main Nazi concentration camps

An interactive timeline of the Third Reich

A Nazi propaganda poster gallery

Biographies of leading Nazis.

